{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":572,"text":"A couple of years ago,"},{"time":2023,"text":"Harvard Business School chose"},{"time":4241,"text":"the best business model of that year."},{"time":6990,"text":"It chose Somali piracy."},{"time":11054,"text":"Pretty much around the same time,"},{"time":13270,"text":"I discovered that there were 544 seafarers"},{"time":19103,"text":"being held hostage on ships,"},{"time":22489,"text":"often anchored just off the Somali coast"},{"time":24579,"text":"in plain sight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27007,"text":"And I learned these two facts, and I thought,"},{"time":29632,"text":"what's going on in shipping?"},{"time":32073,"text":"And I thought, would that happen\nin any other industry?"},{"time":34644,"text":"Would we see 544 airline pilots"},{"time":38155,"text":"held captive in their jumbo jets"},{"time":39785,"text":"on a runway for months, or a year?"},{"time":43272,"text":"Would we see 544 Greyhound bus drivers?"},{"time":47098,"text":"It wouldn't happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":48977,"text":"So I started to get intrigued."},{"time":51755,"text":"And I discovered another fact,"},{"time":54269,"text":"which to me was more astonishing"},{"time":56252,"text":"almost for the fact that I hadn't known it before"},{"time":59337,"text":"at the age of 42, 43."},{"time":61996,"text":"That is how fundamentally \nwe still depend on shipping."},{"time":67315,"text":"Because perhaps the general public"},{"time":69660,"text":"thinks of shipping as an old-fashioned industry,"},{"time":72785,"text":"something brought by sailboat"},{"time":75323,"text":"with Moby Dicks and Jack Sparrows."},{"time":78708,"text":"But shipping isn't that."},{"time":80602,"text":"Shipping is as crucial to us as it has ever been."},{"time":85479,"text":"Shipping brings us 90 percent of world trade."},{"time":90082,"text":"Shipping has quadrupled in size since 1970."},{"time":94647,"text":"We are more dependent on it now than ever."},{"time":97639,"text":"And yet, for such an enormous industry --"},{"time":101398,"text":"there are a 100,000 working vessels on the sea —"},{"time":104875,"text":"it's become pretty much invisible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108268,"text":"Now that sounds absurd in Singapore to say that,"},{"time":112557,"text":"because here shipping is so present"},{"time":114903,"text":"that you stuck a ship on top of a hotel."},{"time":118285,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":119965,"text":"But elsewhere in the world,"},{"time":121981,"text":"if you ask the general public what they know"},{"time":124227,"text":"about shipping and how much\ntrade is carried by sea,"},{"time":127063,"text":"you will get essentially a blank face."},{"time":131680,"text":"You will ask someone on the street"},{"time":133713,"text":"if they've heard of Microsoft."},{"time":135436,"text":"I should think they'll say yes,"},{"time":137273,"text":"because they'll know that they make software"},{"time":139468,"text":"that goes on computers,"},{"time":141363,"text":"and occasionally works."},{"time":144508,"text":"But if you ask them if they've heard of Maersk,"},{"time":148113,"text":"I doubt you'd get the same response,"},{"time":150814,"text":"even though Maersk,"},{"time":152261,"text":"which is just one shipping company amongst many,"},{"time":155952,"text":"has revenues pretty much on a par with Microsoft."},{"time":158934,"text":"[$60.2 billion]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":160415,"text":"Now why is this?"},{"time":162338,"text":"A few years ago,"},{"time":164251,"text":"the first sea lord of the British admiralty --"},{"time":167523,"text":"he is called the first sea lord,"},{"time":169328,"text":"although the chief of the army is not called a land lord —"},{"time":173823,"text":"he said that we, and he meant"},{"time":176266,"text":"in the industrialized nations in the West,"},{"time":178948,"text":"that we suffer from sea blindness."},{"time":182760,"text":"We are blind to the sea"},{"time":184404,"text":"as a place of industry or of work."},{"time":187330,"text":"It's just something we fly over,"},{"time":189623,"text":"a patch of blue on an airline map."},{"time":192628,"text":"Nothing to see, move along."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195953,"text":"So I wanted to open my own eyes"},{"time":199598,"text":"to my own sea blindness,"},{"time":202675,"text":"so I ran away to sea."},{"time":206045,"text":"A couple of years ago, I took a passage"},{"time":208396,"text":"on the Maersk Kendal,"},{"time":210770,"text":"a mid-sized container ship"},{"time":212112,"text":"carrying nearly 7,000 boxes,"},{"time":215340,"text":"and I departed from Felixstowe,"},{"time":217237,"text":"on the south coast of England,"},{"time":219000,"text":"and I ended up right here in Singapore"},{"time":221161,"text":"five weeks later,"},{"time":222654,"text":"considerably less jet-lagged than I am right now."},{"time":227558,"text":"And it was a revelation."},{"time":230800,"text":"We traveled through five seas,"},{"time":232995,"text":"two oceans, nine ports,"},{"time":235542,"text":"and I learned a lot about shipping."}]},{"cues":[{"time":238289,"text":"And one of the first things that surprised me"},{"time":240007,"text":"when I got on board Kendal"},{"time":242394,"text":"was, where are all the people?"},{"time":245139,"text":"I have friends in the Navy who tell me"},{"time":246759,"text":"they sail with 1,000 sailors at a time,"},{"time":249898,"text":"but on Kendal there were only 21 crew."},{"time":253237,"text":"Now that's because shipping is very efficient."},{"time":256114,"text":"Containerization has made it very efficient."},{"time":259178,"text":"Ships have automation now."},{"time":261272,"text":"They can operate with small crews."},{"time":264001,"text":"But it also means that, in the words"},{"time":265790,"text":"of a port chaplain I once met,"},{"time":268250,"text":"the average seafarer you're going to find"},{"time":270295,"text":"on a container ship is either tired or exhausted,"},{"time":274434,"text":"because the pace of modern shipping"},{"time":277213,"text":"is quite punishing for what the shipping calls"},{"time":279534,"text":"its human element,"},{"time":281965,"text":"a strange phrase which they don't seem to realize"},{"time":284417,"text":"sounds a little bit inhuman."},{"time":286821,"text":"So most seafarers now working on container ships"},{"time":289496,"text":"often have less than two hours in port at a time."},{"time":293573,"text":"They don't have time to relax."},{"time":295211,"text":"They're at sea for months at a time,"},{"time":297455,"text":"and even when they're on board,"},{"time":298770,"text":"they don't have access to what"},{"time":300072,"text":"a five-year-old would take for granted, the Internet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":304506,"text":"And another thing that surprised me\nwhen I got on board Kendal"},{"time":307335,"text":"was who I was sitting next to --"},{"time":310327,"text":"Not the queen; I can't imagine why\nthey put me underneath her portrait --"},{"time":315576,"text":"But around that dining table in the officer's saloon,"},{"time":318345,"text":"I was sitting next to a Burmese guy,"},{"time":320173,"text":"I was opposite a Romanian, a Moldavian, an Indian."},{"time":323438,"text":"On the next table was a Chinese guy,"},{"time":325675,"text":"and in the crew room, it was entirely Filipinos."},{"time":328717,"text":"So that was a normal working ship."}]},{"cues":[{"time":331677,"text":"Now how is that possible?"},{"time":333700,"text":"Because the biggest dramatic change"},{"time":335592,"text":"in shipping over the last 60 years,"},{"time":337436,"text":"when most of the general public stopped noticing it,"},{"time":339948,"text":"was something called an open registry,"},{"time":342567,"text":"or a flag of convenience."},{"time":345372,"text":"Ships can now fly the flag of any nation"},{"time":347959,"text":"that provides a flag registry."},{"time":350911,"text":"You can get a flag from the landlocked nation"},{"time":353186,"text":"of Bolivia, or Mongolia,"},{"time":355310,"text":"or North Korea, though that's not very popular."},{"time":358285,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":359708,"text":"So we have these very multinational,"},{"time":361819,"text":"global, mobile crews on ships."},{"time":366600,"text":"And that was a surprise to me."},{"time":369312,"text":"And when we got to pirate waters,"},{"time":372429,"text":"down the Bab-el-Mandeb strait\nand into the Indian Ocean,"},{"time":375555,"text":"the ship changed."},{"time":377307,"text":"And that was also shocking, because suddenly,"},{"time":380450,"text":"I realized, as the captain said to me,"},{"time":382664,"text":"that I had been crazy to choose to go"},{"time":384666,"text":"through pirate waters on a container ship."},{"time":387718,"text":"We were no longer allowed on deck."},{"time":389709,"text":"There were double pirate watches."},{"time":392305,"text":"And at that time, there were those \n544 seafarers being held hostage,"},{"time":396582,"text":"and some of them were held hostage for years"},{"time":398550,"text":"because of the nature of shipping\nand the flag of convenience."},{"time":401321,"text":"Not all of them, but some of them were,"},{"time":403403,"text":"because for the minority\nof unscrupulous ship owners,"},{"time":408117,"text":"it can be easy to hide behind"},{"time":410662,"text":"the anonymity offered by some flags of convenience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":415661,"text":"What else does our sea blindness mask?"},{"time":419600,"text":"Well, if you go out to sea on a ship"},{"time":421919,"text":"or on a cruise ship, and look up to the funnel,"},{"time":423914,"text":"you'll see very black smoke."},{"time":426783,"text":"And that's because shipping"},{"time":429318,"text":"has very tight margins,\nand they want cheap fuel,"},{"time":431905,"text":"so they use something called bunker fuel,"},{"time":434076,"text":"which was described to me\nby someone in the tanker industry"},{"time":436592,"text":"as the dregs of the refinery,"},{"time":438758,"text":"or just one step up from asphalt."},{"time":442015,"text":"And shipping is the greenest method of transport."},{"time":445412,"text":"In terms of carbon emissions per ton per mile,"},{"time":447755,"text":"it emits about a thousandth of aviation"},{"time":450726,"text":"and about a tenth of trucking."},{"time":452841,"text":"But it's not benign, because there's so much of it."},{"time":456077,"text":"So shipping emissions are\nabout three to four percent,"},{"time":458607,"text":"almost the same as aviation's."},{"time":460782,"text":"And if you put shipping emissions"},{"time":462171,"text":"on a list of the countries' carbon emissions,"},{"time":465551,"text":"it would come in about sixth,"},{"time":467164,"text":"somewhere near Germany."},{"time":469278,"text":"It was calculated in 2009 that the 15 largest ships"},{"time":473296,"text":"pollute in terms of particles and soot"},{"time":475891,"text":"and noxious gases"},{"time":477291,"text":"as much as all the cars in the world."},{"time":479869,"text":"And the good news is that"},{"time":481269,"text":"people are now talking about sustainable shipping."},{"time":483464,"text":"There are interesting initiatives going on."},{"time":485951,"text":"But why has it taken so long?"},{"time":488206,"text":"When are we going to start talking and thinking"},{"time":490553,"text":"about shipping miles as well as air miles?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":494589,"text":"I also traveled to Cape Cod to look"},{"time":497394,"text":"at the plight of the North Atlantic right whale,"},{"time":501321,"text":"because this to me was one\nof the most surprising things"},{"time":503477,"text":"about my time at sea,"},{"time":505433,"text":"and what it made me think about."},{"time":507230,"text":"We know about man's impact on the ocean"},{"time":510383,"text":"in terms of fishing and overfishing,"},{"time":512815,"text":"but we don't really know much about"},{"time":514623,"text":"what's happening underneath the water."},{"time":516806,"text":"And in fact, shipping has a role to play here,"},{"time":519411,"text":"because shipping noise has contributed"},{"time":523057,"text":"to damaging the acoustic\nhabitats of ocean creatures."},{"time":526250,"text":"Light doesn't penetrate beneath\nthe surface of the water,"},{"time":529242,"text":"so ocean creatures like whales and dolphins"},{"time":531869,"text":"and even 800 species of fish"},{"time":534173,"text":"communicate by sound."},{"time":537064,"text":"And a North Atlantic right whale"},{"time":538777,"text":"can transmit across hundreds of miles."},{"time":541984,"text":"A humpback can transmit a sound"},{"time":543947,"text":"across a whole ocean."},{"time":545885,"text":"But a supertanker can also be heard"},{"time":547840,"text":"coming across a whole ocean,"},{"time":549911,"text":"and because the noise that\npropellers make underwater"},{"time":552475,"text":"is sometimes at the same frequency that whales use,"},{"time":555812,"text":"then it can damage their acoustic habitat,"},{"time":558846,"text":"and they need this for breeding,"},{"time":560536,"text":"for finding feeding grounds,"},{"time":562187,"text":"for finding mates."},{"time":564710,"text":"And the acoustic habitat of the\nNorth Atlantic right whale"},{"time":567551,"text":"has been reduced by up to 90 percent."},{"time":570901,"text":"But there are no laws governing \nacoustic pollution yet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575513,"text":"And when I arrived in Singapore,"},{"time":578769,"text":"and I apologize for this, but I \ndidn't want to get off my ship."},{"time":583676,"text":"I'd really loved being on board Kendal."},{"time":586635,"text":"I'd been well treated by the crew,"},{"time":588530,"text":"I'd had a garrulous and entertaining captain,"},{"time":592071,"text":"and I would happily have signed up\nfor another five weeks,"},{"time":596143,"text":"something that the captain also said"},{"time":597974,"text":"I was crazy to think about."},{"time":600247,"text":"But I wasn't there for nine months at a time"},{"time":602491,"text":"like the Filipino seafarers,"},{"time":604446,"text":"who, when I asked them to describe their job to me,"},{"time":606685,"text":"called it \"dollar for homesickness.\""},{"time":609007,"text":"They had good salaries,"},{"time":610485,"text":"but theirs is still an isolating and difficult life"},{"time":613516,"text":"in a dangerous and often difficult element."}]},{"cues":[{"time":617205,"text":"But when I get to this part, I'm in two minds,"},{"time":619291,"text":"because I want to salute those seafarers"},{"time":622216,"text":"who bring us 90 percent of everything"},{"time":624403,"text":"and get very little thanks or recognition for it."},{"time":628069,"text":"I want to salute the 100,000 ships"},{"time":630790,"text":"that are at sea"},{"time":632113,"text":"that are doing that work, coming in and out"},{"time":634646,"text":"every day, bringing us what we need."},{"time":637875,"text":"But I also want to see shipping,"},{"time":640895,"text":"and us, the general public,\nwho know so little about it,"},{"time":644374,"text":"to have a bit more scrutiny,"},{"time":646414,"text":"to be a bit more transparent,"},{"time":648518,"text":"to have 90 percent transparency."},{"time":651790,"text":"Because I think we could all benefit"},{"time":654691,"text":"from doing something very simple,"},{"time":656796,"text":"which is learning to see the sea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":659878,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":662036,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}